{
  "texts": [
    "The formal local system associated to V is the local system on ⟨z 3 /3⟩ with trivial monodromy, which we view again as glued from one-dimensional constant sheaves (with stalk C) on 6 sectors.",
    "The Legendre transform maps the circle ⟨z 3 /3⟩ onto ⟨ 2 3 w 3/2 ⟩.",
    "On the left: The formal local system before Fourier transform.",
    "On the right: The formal local system after Fourier transform.",
    "The numbers in the circles show the identification of sectors given by Legendre transform."
  ]
}